The course is meant mainly for foreign students. During the course the development of social rights - right to work and to social security - in Estonia will be dealt with. The development will be observed starting from the re-independence till to present day. Main purpose is to give to the students an overview about the development and protection of social rights in transition country. Also the principles of legal regulation of social security and labour relations in Estonia will be dealt with.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Aim of the course is to give to the students knowledge about the Estonian labour law and social security law, about the constitutional guarantees of the right to work and right to social security in Estonia.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  At the end of the course a student is able to: 
- characterise constitutional guarantees for the right to work and right to social security in Estonia; 
- explain different institutes of Estonian labour law and the principles of legal regulation of employment relations in Estonia; 
- explain different institutes of Estonian social security law and the principles of legal regulation social security.
